# Specification Structure Rule

When creating or updating requirement specifications:

- Requirement docs live in `spec/requirements/` as Markdown `.md`.
- Use hierarchy `Feature -> Use Case -> Story -> Item` without skipping levels.
- Every Use Case/Story/Item heading must carry one status label (`Spec`, `Ready`, `Impl`, `QA`, `Done`).
- Requirement specifications under `spec/requirements/` must be written in German.
- Keep `doc/specification-manual.qmd` synchronized if structure/system conventions change.
